<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-09-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-05-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="380" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d380">
                                <head><hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi></head>
                                <p>According to the Log, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_470">p. 470</ref>, this dinner meeting lasted
                                    until 10:30 p.m. No official minutes of the conversation appear
                                    to have been prepared, but a memorandum prepared by <persName corresp="#p_BCE2">Bohlen</persName> a few days later (<hi rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_838">p. 838</ref>)
                                    indicates that the Declaration on Iran and the Conference
                                    communiqué were discussed and put into final form.</p>
                            </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>